data.output: the sun was shining, there was a gentle breeze and I was enjoying the drive through the countryside.   i was on my way to join other members of the Petrol Head Club for a fun day out.    I was wearing my favourite Diesel jeans and club T-shirt - i thought i looked great.    i switched radio channels to the Pump fm and sang alon

The letter sat amongst others on the mat at the empty house, i was about to show to the clients.     The musty smell around the house was tickling my nose and i could see spiders.  Should I stamp on them or pick them up with one of the letters and send them on their way in the garden.

The sound of the mouth organ played by the beggar on the street was delightful.  He had a good position, just outside the Empire cinema which had been closed for years.   I had heard that the Fire Brigade had it closed down as it did not comply with fire regulations

The payment was overdue, i knew it but i didn't care.    I could exist without the internet for a few days if they cut me off.   Maybe, it would make me happier to live without it.     I wouldnt have these feelings of dread and gloom at what i might see when i open up my tablet
